image_analysis.description: A photograph of a narrow utility or electrical room. The room contains various electrical panels, conduits, and wiring. A yellow 'Louisville' brand ladder is leaning against the left wall. There is a large white electrical cabinet on the right side, along with several vertical metal conduits. A black insulated pipe runs vertically. In the background, more electrical panels and wiring are visible on a plywood wall. A small wire cart with a white telephone is on the floor to the right. The floor is a reddish-brown color.
image_analysis.layout: Narrow corridor perspective looking into a utility room.

notes: The image is a photograph included in a document set, identified by the Bates stamp EFTA00001139. The text 'Louisville' is a brand name on a ladder.
